I never ever comment on YouTube videos but I can’t help myself today. 

People really need to get over the idea that “living together” is the end of the world. 

Two people should enter a marriage (a life long commitment) knowing the good bad and ugly about each other. 
If Phera or Nikaah is the only thing keeping you in the marriage then you are in the WRONG relationship. 
Commitment is a choice you make everyday for the rest of your life and you have every right to know if the person who you are committing to “forever” is actually who they say they are. People change a lot once you start living together, their real face comes out. 

What if they are a liar? Cheater? They can have anger problems, or anything. This is not our parents generation where they stay in unhappy marriage. 

As long at both people are adults, safe, and consent they should spend as much time as possible getting to know each other.
